description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Temporary Staffing service for a Booking Administrator, Band 2 on a 6 month fixed term contract to join our established team, servicing all specialisms throughout Somerset NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is critical in supporting the wider trust to maintain safer staffing levels through providing support for the Temporary Staffing Consultants and being the first point of contact for all bank and agency colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful candidate will be organised, efficient and have excellent customer service skills. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy, pro-active team and therefore, we require an individual who demonstrates strong communication skills and flexibility in their approach to the working day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;T&lt;strong&gt;here will a large call volume so you must be confident to switch between responsibilities dependant on the service need.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time role and will be remote working at present, therefore we are looking for someone who is willing to learn and develop their skills as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The working hours will be Monday - Friday 9am - 5pm.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous experience working within the NHS and/or similar environments and using Allocate Bank Staff are desirable but not essential, as a full training package will be provided.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dee Barber, Temporary Staffing Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;dee.barber@somersetft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07787 271287&lt;/p&gt;
